      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Leaf warblers — small, active, largely green or yellow-green warblers that glean insects from foliage with remarkable agility. The willow warbler is the single most numerous summer bird in Sweden, estimated at over 40 million breeding pairs across Scandinavia. Despite weighing just 9 grams, it completes an annual round trip of 10,000–14,000 km to sub-Saharan Africa and back. The genus spans the entire Palearctic from Atlantic Europe to the Pacific, with diversity peaking in the Himalayas and China.",
